iews. This is the most persistent issue. Components constantly use hardcoded hex
values like `0x4a9eff`, `0x333333`, `#dddddd`, `#888888`, `#aaaaaa`, etc. instea
d of UITheme constants. The existing docs already have F-07 but it's clearly not
enough. Need to strengthen the guidance.\n\n2. **Emoji/character as icons (F-01)
** - Repeated in reviews 3, 4, 5. Using `add.text` with emoji or unicode charact
ers instead of texture keys. The PRD-004 defines `icon?: string` as texture key 
name but components implement it as text rendering.\n\n3. **`createFallbackRect`
vs `createInkBackground` misuse** - Reviews 2, 4, 5 repeatedly flag this. The di
stinction is:\n   - `createFallbackRect` = texture missing scenario (prints warn
)\n   - `createInkBackground` = normal default rendering (no warn)\n   But this 
isn't clearly documented in the Foundation/Component layers.\n\n4. **Depth value
s / magic numbers** - Reviews 3, 4, 5 mention using hardcoded depth values like 
`this.setDepth(1000)` instead of `UIDepthLayer.UI`, or wrong depth values (Dialo
g=5000 instead of 3000, Toast=4000 instead of 5000). The 01-foundation.md has a 
depth table but doesn't clearly map to `UIDepthLayer` enum.\n\n5. **Animation tw
een killTweensOf** - Reviews 3, 4, 5. Components don't call `killTweensOf` befor
e adding new tweens. The 01-foundation.md mentions this in 1.3 but perhaps needs
to be more explicit with code examples.\n\n6. **Boolean parameter naming (isXxx)
** - Reviews 2, 3, 4. PRD-004 requires `isXxx` but existing code uses `disabled`
, `autoHide`, `interactive`. Need to document this migration.\n\n7. **Fluorescen
t colors in UITheme** - Review 4, 5. `emeraldGreen`, `coralRed` were added to UI
Theme but violate F-04. Need to strengthen F-04 guidance.\n\n8. **Origin inconsi
stency between `createInkBackground` and `createFallbackRect`** - Review 1 menti
ons this. The functions should behave consistently (`setOrigin(0.5)`).\n\nLet me
check what the existing `docs/spec-evolution-28` branch has, if anything.",
    encrypted=None
)
